    {
      "id": "1181611182882353152",
      "text": "Alright, nerds\n\nI filed a FOIA appeal and won the infamous NROL-39 surveillance satellite logo as a PDF.\n\nhttps://t.co/GypoZPnwsu\n\nThis ain't a scanned powerpoint. This is a resizable vector. You know what you must do. Unleash the swag. https://t.co/WZJXeBdHPi",
      "createdAt": "2019-10-08T16:43:53.000Z",
      "likeCount": 2195,
      "mediaCount": 1,
      "isReply": false,
      "media": [
        "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EGXs53VUcAA3qa0.jpg"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "985179795771211776",
      "text": "The new @latimes owner is moving the newsroom from its historic HQ to El Segundo.\n\nI've been lucky enough to inhabit and explore the interlocking buildings at 1st and Spring for over a decade.\n\nI'd like to share it with you. It's a beautiful day in #DTLA. Shall we take a wander? https://t.co/PYnRwVraHf",
      "createdAt": "2018-04-14T15:35:41.000Z",
      "likeCount": 1534,
      "mediaCount": 1,
      "isReply": false,
      "media": [
        "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DawPy1PUMAARPJ4.jpg"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "1288995784826871808",
      "text": "In 1894, the @latimes launched a carrier pigeon service that ferried news back and forth between downtown LA and Catalina Island.\n\nThe byline included the pigeon. https://t.co/KuWqkG1u37",
      "createdAt": "2020-07-31T00:31:58.000Z",
      "likeCount": 1203,
      "mediaCount": 4,
      "isReply": false,
      "media": [
        "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EeNuuNXUMAADGEP.png",
